The PAN national leader declared that the former Panist party chairman had the right to appeal to the National Order Commission and demand what the law allowed him.
The national leader of the PAN, César Nava Vázquez, assured that the expulsion of Manuel Espino Barrientos was legal and that the former PAN party chairman had the right to appeal to the National Order Commission and demand what the law allowed him.
In an interview conducted before the appeal, Gabino Cué Monteagudos, as governor of the state, explained that the expulsion of Espinos was a decision made at the local level.
